<subSubSection id="C349651EFFEAFFBAB5B9FBB7FC0DFE30" lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="38" pageNumber="112" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFEAFFB4B5B9FBB7FEBEFBD1" blockId="38.[189,310,1106,1132]" box="[189,310,1106,1132]" pageId="38" pageNumber="112">
<heading id="D0A481F9FFEAFFB4B5B9FBB7FEBEFBD1" bold="true" box="[189,310,1106,1132]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="38" pageNumber="112" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEAFFB4B5B9FBB7FEBEFBD1" bold="true" box="[189,310,1106,1132]" pageId="38" pageNumber="112">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFEAFFB4B5B9FB64FAF0FB03" blockId="38.[189,1400,1153,1215]" pageId="38" pageNumber="112">
This species is closest to 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFEAFFB4B4EAFB64FD1BFB26" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1927" box="[494,659,1153,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkimensis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEAFFB4B4EAFB64FD1BFB26" box="[494,659,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="112">S. sikkimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFEAFFB4B7CBFB64FBB3FB26" authority="Cockerell, 1911" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1911" box="[719,1083,1153,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEAFFB4B7CBFB64FCFFFB26" box="[719,887,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="112">S. formosanus</emphasis>
Cockerell, 1911
</taxonomicName>
by a combination of large body size (more than 
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFEAFFB4B4C9FB41FD91FB02" box="[461,537,1188,1215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="38" pageNumber="112" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
), costal margin with at least nine hamuli and the presence of a lateral
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2C661DFFEAFFB4B5B9F845FE1CF863" pageId="38" pageNumber="112" startId="38.[189,232,1952,1978]" targetBox="[189,1397,1285,1908]" targetPageId="38">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFEAFFB4B5B9F845FE1CF863" blockId="38.[189,1399,1952,2014]" pageId="38" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEAFFB4B5B9F845FE93F807" bold="true" box="[189,283,1952,1978]" pageId="38" pageNumber="112">Fig. 21.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFEAFFB4B421F845FD98F807" box="[293,528,1952,1978]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uttaricus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEAFFB4B421F845FD98F807" box="[293,528,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="112">Sphecodes uttaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21457FCFFEAFFB4B71DF844FDFDF806" box="[537,629,1953,1979]" pageId="38" pageNumber="112" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Holotype, ♀ (PCMS/OLBL). Habitus in lateral view and labels. Scale bar = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF2C661DFFEBFFB5B5B9F865FE6CF85C" pageId="39" pageNumber="113" startId="39.[189,232,1920,1946]" targetBox="[189,1398,325,1819]" targetPageId="39">
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFEBFFB5B5B9F865FE6CF85C" blockId="39.[188,1399,1920,2017]" pageId="39" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEBFFB5B5B9F865FEA9F827" bold="true" box="[189,289,1920,1946]" pageId="39" pageNumber="113">Fig. 22.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFEBFFB5B435F865FDADF827" box="[305,549,1920,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uttaricus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEBFFB5B435F865FDADF827" box="[305,549,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="113">Sphecodes uttaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21457FCFFEBFFB5B731F864FD10F826" box="[565,664,1921,1947]" pageId="39" pageNumber="113" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Holotype, ♀ (PCMS/OLBL). 
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEBFFB5B11AF865FBBBF827" bold="true" box="[1054,1075,1920,1946]" pageId="39" pageNumber="113">A</emphasis>
. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEBFFB5B5B9F841FF7CF800" bold="true" box="[189,244,1955,1982]" pageId="39" pageNumber="113">B–C</emphasis>
. Head in frontal (B) and lateral view (C). 
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEBFFB5B7DFF841FD78F803" bold="true" box="[731,752,1956,1982]" pageId="39" pageNumber="113">D</emphasis>
. Metasoma in dorso-lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFEBFFB5B178F841FB18F803" bold="true" box="[1148,1168,1956,1982]" pageId="39" pageNumber="113">E</emphasis>
. T1 in dorso-lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFE4FFBAB5B9FEECFC0DFE30" blockId="40.[188,1399,265,397]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">
preocipital carina. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFE4FFBAB7F5FEECFC1CFE9E" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1927" box="[753,916,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkimensis">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFE4FFBAB7F5FEECFC1CFE9E" box="[753,916,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">S. sikkimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having fewer hamuli (9–10 vs 12–15) and a smaller body size (
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFE4FFBAB4D8FEC9FDCEFEFA" box="[476,582,300,327]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="40" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5 mm</quantity>
vs 
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFE4FFBAB769FEC9FD65FEFA" box="[621,749,300,327]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="40" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15 mm</quantity>
) and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D16FFE4FFBAB66FFEC8FB99FEFB" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1911" box="[875,1041,300,327]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFE4FFBAB66FFEC8FB99FEFB" box="[875,1041,300,327]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">S. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by having sparse and mixed punctation of T1 with coarse (15–25 μm / 0.5–3) and microscopical punctures (5 μm) (vs dense and coarse punctures separated by 0.5–1 puncture diameter).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C349651EFFE4FFBAB5B9FE51FABCFE41" box="[189,1332,436,509]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114" type="etymology">
