<heading id="D0A481F9FFE4FFBAB5B9FD3FFEC6FD49" bold="true" box="[189,334,730,756]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="114" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFE4FFBAB5B9FD3FFEC6FD49" bold="true" box="[189,334,730,756]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFE4FFBAB5EEFCECFDA1FC9E" blockId="40.[189,705,777,839]" box="[234,553,777,803]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFE4FFBAB5EEFCECFECDFC9E" bold="true" box="[234,325,777,803]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54E88837FFE4FFBAB451FCECFE48FC9E" box="[341,448,777,803]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFE4FFBAB4C8FCECFDA8FC9E" box="[460,544,777,803]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="38.[189,232,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,1285,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-245@38.[189,1398,1283,1908]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="Fig. 21. Sphecodes uttaricus sp. nov. Holotype, ♀ (PCMS/OLBL). Habitus in lateral view and labels. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFE4FFBAB5B9FCC8FD49FCFA" blockId="40.[189,705,777,839]" box="[189,705,812,839]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">
MEASUREMENTS. Total body length 
<quantity id="4CAB9B70FFE4FFBAB755FCC9FD34FCFA" box="[593,700,812,839]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="40" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFE4FFBAB5B9FC8BFC2DFBC3" blockId="40.[186,1399,877,1150]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">
HEAD (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFE4FFBAB409FC88FEE9FC35" box="[269,353,877,904]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,325,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-13@39.[189,1398,325,1819]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 22. Sphecodes uttaricus sp. nov. Holotype, ♀ (PCMS/OLBL). A. Mesosoma, dorsal view. B–C. Head in frontal (B) and lateral view (C). D. Metasoma in dorso-lateral view. E. T1 in dorso-lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
B–C). Black; transverse, ca 1.25 times as wide as long; lateral preoccipital carina present, well-developed; vertex elevated, distance from top of head to upper margin of lateral ocellus ca 1.5 ocellar diameter as seen in frontal view and ca two diameters as seen in dorsal view; mandibles bi-dentate; F1 0.5 times as long as wide; F2 0.7 times as long as wide; F3 1.1 times as long as wide; supraclypeal area bulging; frons and paraocular area mostly with confluent punctures; ocello-ocular area densely punctate with confluent punctures and punctures separated by at most a half puncture diameter (30–50 μm); clypeus sparser punctate with shiny, smooth interspaces equal to at most a puncture diameter; paraocular area and gena with dense plumose setae, obscuring integument.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFE4FFBAB5B9FB43FE0EFA2E" blockId="40.[188,1399,1189,1427]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">
MESOSOMA. Mesosoma (including legs) black; wings with strong brownish darkening and metallic violet luster; stigma and veins dark brown; hind wing with the angle between basal (
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFE4FFBAB187FB2CFB13FB5F" box="[1155,1179,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">M</emphasis>
) and cubital (
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFE4FFBAB04EFB2CFAE4FB5E" box="[1354,1388,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Cu</emphasis>
) veins ca 70°, costal margin with nine hamuli; mesoscutum and mesoscutellum (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFE4FFBAB16AFB09FB52FABB" box="[1134,1242,1260,1286]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,325,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-13@39.[189,1398,325,1819]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 22. Sphecodes uttaricus sp. nov. Holotype, ♀ (PCMS/OLBL). A. Mesosoma, dorsal view. B–C. Head in frontal (B) and lateral view (C). D. Metasoma in dorso-lateral view. E. T1 in dorso-lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Fig. 22A</figureCitation>
) densely and coarsely punctate (50–100 μm), with confluent punctures peripherally and medially with punctures separated by at most a puncture diameter; hypoepimeral area and mesepisternum coarsely reticulaterugose; propodeal triangle (metapostnotum) roughly reticulate-rugose (sculpture forming 2–3 rows of large deep cells).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFE4FFBAB5B9FA5EFBCAF9DC" blockId="40.[187,1399,1466,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">
METASOMA. Metasomal T1 on disc with coarse punctures (15–25 μm) separated by 0.5–3 puncture diameters and laterally with numerous tiny punctures (ca 5 μm) between them, marginal zone sparsely and finely punctate, impunctate along posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFE4FFBAB642F9E5FC27F9A6" box="[838,943,1536,1563]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,325,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-13@39.[189,1398,325,1819]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 22. Sphecodes uttaricus sp. nov. Holotype, ♀ (PCMS/OLBL). A. Mesosoma, dorsal view. B–C. Head in frontal (B) and lateral view (C). D. Metasoma in dorso-lateral view. E. T1 in dorso-lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Fig. 22E</figureCitation>
); remainder of terga similarly punctate, but denser and with impunctate marginal zones (
<figureCitation id="13682A10FFE4FFBAB7EEF9C1FCDEF983" box="[746,854,1572,1598]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,325,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-13@39.[189,1398,325,1819]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 22. Sphecodes uttaricus sp. nov. Holotype, ♀ (PCMS/OLBL). A. Mesosoma, dorsal view. B–C. Head in frontal (B) and lateral view (C). D. Metasoma in dorso-lateral view. E. T1 in dorso-lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Fig. 22D</figureCitation>
); pygidial plate dull, as wide as metabasitarsus; T1–T4 red; sterna finely tessellate to smooth with coarse shallow setal pores.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC3695FFE4FFBAB5EEF96DFEA2F91F" blockId="40.[189,313,1672,1733]" box="[234,298,1672,1698]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="B927EA87FFE4FFBAB5EEF96DFEA2F91F" bold="true" box="[234,298,1672,1698]" pageId="40" pageNumber="114">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
